The thing I like most in the #photos I take and in the #videos I record is the #story I want to tell or my point of view, in a nutshell what the content represents for me. 
Having made this small premise, I'll tell you what this photo represents for me. 
When I'm down in my mood, I don't usually seek #attention, I tend to close in on #myself.
In these #moments Max, my #dog, helps me to have fun.
First of all he #understands that I'm sick, and he begins to take my hand with his mouth to take me out, and so every time we go.
This photo is based on the #feeling, as if Max were the light in the middle of the #darkness of my emotions.  maybe I exaggerate, but every time I see him it warms my #heart.

caption.text:
I was recently asked how one finds their gifts. This a question that I have posed myself in the past and prompted me to share my experience.

First off I would recommend taking @lianashanti’s Awakening Ancient Gifts course which was a huge catalyst for me. The journeys she includes have facilitated a deeper connection to myself.  

The second thing is you need to shift your attitude if you think this is an external process. We are not discovering our gifts but REDISCOVERING them. This is because they have always been there with us but due to wounding, our shadow, conditioning, programming and all the junk that our body, mind and soul gets lumbered with, we are unable to connect with our gifts. Liana has rightly said that everything we need is within us. All the healing work you do needs to lead back to you.

So here are some notes on what has helped me and my experience so far:

1. What did you want to be as a child? This is a question that will help you connect to your Inner Children and those unadulterated dreams you had. Even if there were a ton of things you wanted to do, if you write them down there will be clues and pattern which emerge.

2. What do people always say you’re good at? I’ve been told my whole life that I would be a great teacher. Whilst I used to eye-roll because I had my own filters on what that meant, I see it in a different way now. So even though you may not always enjoy the things you are good at, try not to attach it to a job or role. See the talent or skill behind it.
 
3. Directly and humbly ask to be shown your path. Ask for the help and guidance to be shown your gifts for the highest good of yourself and service to others.
 
4. Nurture a direct relationship with God (Universe/Source etc). This is connected to point 3 and may be triggering for some people – including me once upon a time. If you still have sovereignty over your soul then you have a direct hotline to God. Remove the “gatekeepers” because you don’t need them. Gatekeepers can be Churches, or things like Tarot. These are all easily hijacked. Use your direct connection to God!

(Cont in comments)

preview_comments.text:
5. What challenges have you overcome? Weightloss? OCD? Shoplifting? Narc abuse? This is part of your medicine. It doesn’t matter if there are endless weight loss coaches because only YOU have a unique perspective or voice which will resonate with the right people. The condition here is that you need to be fully authentic in that truth. You don’t have to be the “perfect” finished article, you just need to show up with what you can offer moment to moment. This is a piece of advice I’ve heard @cahira_noelani say to @healthmasteryinstitute students time and time again.
 
6. Watch out for the clues. Perhaps it’s a teaching, a quote, an animal messenger. Use your discernment because not everything is a message and don’t invest in things that make your ego feel good. The right message will find you.
 
7. Find your Power Animal. If you’re accurately able to find it out I recommend it. A Power Animal is assigned to you from birth. They’re a representation of their entire species. Learn as much as you can about them (environment, mating, behaviours) because it also holds clues to your own characteristics and strengths.
 
8. Take daily action. Whether it is working a little bit more on your business, investing 30 mins to walk during lunch or just spending time with your children or spouse for a meaningful interaction. “The Universe rewards action” and you’ll be adjusted and steered closer to your gifts when you take action.
